{"name":"Marshal","type":"subclass","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Peacekeepers, bounty hunters, and thief-catchers, the marshal knows how to track their enemy and catch it off-guard to bring it down.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc30\"><span><strong>Combat Research</strong></span></h4><p>At 2nd level, you gain the Scout sphere as a bonus sphere. You deal an additional +1d4 damage with all damage rolls made against targets you have scouted.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc31\"><span><strong>Favored Enemy</strong></span></h4><p>At 6th level, you may choose a favored enemy, as a ranger. You gain a new favored enemy at 14th level as well.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc32\"><span><strong>Greater Combat Research</strong></span></h4><p>Beginning at 10th level, your combat research damage increases to +1d6, and you always count as having scouted any member of your favored enemies.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc33\"><span><strong>Masterful Combat Research</strong></span></h4><p>At 14th level, your combat research damage increases to +1d8.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","identifier":"marshal","classIdentifier":"conscript","advancement":[{"_id":"TOS4gRWP3Y4hcQM4","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.l8NIBgp3A4z1mGU8"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":2,"title":"Features"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.ak3mudprtTkKvReM"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":6,"title":"Features","_id":"VZuhWXtdAnsqbJkN"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.sIYRhXjk1FBHXfVw"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":10,"title":"Features","_id":"WYqA4ExO2Us6wWb6"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.OtLAZorrnX0r2sYn"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":14,"title":"Features","_id":"hwmRuUsDn0IFBHF2"}],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Gf5wJyDCkzoUZtN9"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685725409895,"modifiedTime":1685725685056,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"cP9HXr6ghjcn0CXX"}
{"name":"Path of the Doomblade","type":"subclass","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>The path of the doomblade blends the cataclysmic power of destruction with the precision of martial prowess.</p><h4 id=\"toc31\"><span><strong>@UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.NRZaCdBr9hTf12GY]{Blended Training}</strong></span></h4><p>At 2nd level, you gain Blade (blast shape) as a bonus magic talent. If you already possess the Blade (blast shape) talent, you gain an additional talent from the Destruction sphere. Any time you would gain a magic talent from levels in elementalist, you can instead gain a martial talent.</p><h4 id=\"toc32\"><span><strong>@UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.Xjlb6PmzU2U9L2m0]{Magus}</strong></span></h4><p>At 3rd level, when you cast an unaugmented destructive blast with the Blade (blast shape) on ammunition or weapons only you are using, you can use the Magus feature to have the effect persist for the remainder of the duration without concentration. Destructive blasts that you used the Magus feature on cannot be augmented further, and the effect ends on any ammunition or weapon that is not in your hand or on your body at the end of your turn.</p><h4 id=\"toc33\"><span><strong>@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.classfeatures.XogoBnFWmCAHXppo]{Extra Attack}</strong></span></h4><p>Starting at 6th level, you can attack twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.</p><h4 id=\"toc34\"><span><strong>@UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.B0kkkea55wngmOmN]{Greater Magus}</strong></span></h4><p>At 11th level, when you make a special attack with the Blade (blast shape), you can inflict its secondary or rider effect without having to use a bonus action.</p><h4 id=\"toc35\"><span><strong>@UUID[Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.zE9ezGs6MxJsJFyJ]{Destructive Mastery}</strong></span></h4><p>At 17th level, you can cast any destructive blast as a bonus action.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","identifier":"doomblade","classIdentifier":"elementalist","advancement":[{"_id":"UGuOBpqnmGN2JxKx","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.NRZaCdBr9hTf12GY"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":2,"title":"Features"},{"_id":"JkmClxrFmTEvn8uc","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.Xjlb6PmzU2U9L2m0"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":3,"title":"Features"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5e.classfeatures.XogoBnFWmCAHXppo"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":6,"title":"Features","_id":"HQHShioJ3AQXpvku"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.B0kkkea55wngmOmN"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":11,"title":"Features","_id":"B1uePEkGD7kg9osX"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.zE9ezGs6MxJsJFyJ"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":17,"title":"Features","_id":"1uY2GDzAeobDGIBJ"}],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iRvqY9jCCZqrfkj6"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685620719501,"modifiedTime":1685621515192,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"ckSZT2eqvFGmT7dk"}
{"name":"Battleborn (Spheres of Might)","type":"subclass","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>There are times when someone’s body does everything perfectly; the lines of motion converge to allow the warrior to jump higher, strike faster, and dodge more completely than most humanoids are normally capable of. For the battleborn, these moments of genius are not the exception, but the norm. This subclass requires Spheres of Might.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc26\"><span><strong>Natural Talents</strong></span></h4><p>At 2nd level, you gain 1 martial talent. Whenever you complete a long rest, you can change this talent. You gain an additional talent that you can change in this fashion at 10th and 18th levels.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc27\"><span><strong>Inspired Hit</strong></span></h4><p>At 5th level, your weapon and spell attack rolls score a critical hit on a roll of 19 or 20.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc28\"><span><strong>Natural Inspiration</strong></span></h4><p>At 10th level, you can change your natural talents during a short or long rest.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc29\"><span><strong>Greater Extra Attack</strong></span></h4><p>At 14th level, you can make three attacks instead of two when making an Attack action.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc30\"><span><strong>Masterful Inspiration</strong></span></h4><p>Beginning at 18th level, you can spend a spell point to change a natural talent as a bonus action.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc31\"><span><strong>Genius Hit</strong></span></h4><p>Beginning at 20th level, your weapon and spell attack rolls score a critical hit on a roll of 18-20.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sphres of Power","identifier":"battleborn-spheres","classIdentifier":"prodigy","advancement":[{"_id":"KizCImelz0cLOWNQ","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.LnlVCGhaq1pM2HKc"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":2,"title":"Features"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.KbY2x4QzxpYBLe2p"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":10,"title":"Features","_id":"mTSDsiXe0J7tp9pt"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.ccruJvGZMyCAjjse"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":5,"title":"Features","_id":"k8o7twAJl6RbOwd1"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.5BjtUvo6YhyeHuCu"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":14,"title":"Features","_id":"5QM8MCumuiAIrMjP"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.XHiZX3GfwNXyMEbj"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":18,"title":"Features","_id":"Qle5LR8y5Gj0ZMN5"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.By3bnSW91Jh6UxW8"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":20,"title":"Features","_id":"IdmoDzzXxADAbQK6"}],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Qsokg0kMdiPy0IUB"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685723363178,"modifiedTime":1685723846421,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"gGlUxFoCzGyubbgf"}
{"name":"Soothsayer","type":"subclass","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Soothsayers speak predictions and explain the will of Fate.</p><h4 id=\"toc49\"><span><strong>Portent</strong></span></h4><p>Starting at 2nd level, glimpses of the future begin to press in on your awareness. When you finish a long rest, roll two d20s and record the numbers rolled. You can replace any attack roll, saving throw, or ability check made by you or a creature that you can see with one of these foretelling rolls. You must choose to do so before the roll, and you can replace a roll in this way only once per turn.</p><p>Each foretelling roll can be used only once. When you finish a long rest, you lose any unused foretelling rolls.</p><h4 id=\"toc50\"><span><strong>Diviner’s Eye</strong></span></h4><p>Beginning at 6th level, whenever you spend 2 or more spell points on a Divination sphere effect, reduce the spell point cost by 1. This is applied after Master of Magic (meaning at 20th level, a 3 spell point effect would only cost you 1 spell point).</p><h4 id=\"toc51\"><span><strong>Master of Fate</strong></span></h4><p>At 10th level, when applying a motif to yourself, you may grant yourself two motifs at once. You must spend any spell points for each motif individually, but if you are maintaining the effect through concentration, you may maintain both motifs as if they were a single effect.</p><h4 id=\"toc52\"><span><strong>Greater Portent</strong></span></h4><p>Starting at 14th level, the visions in your dreams intensify and paint a more accurate picture in your mind of what is to come. You roll three d20s for your Portent feature, rather than two.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spheres of Power","identifier":"soothsayer","classIdentifier":"incanter","advancement":[{"_id":"w82P9WMjfgOphyS6","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.aaDCdplpnjG0B6zp"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":2,"title":"Features"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.HQZk7jpwF8IjpLY1"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":6,"title":"Features","_id":"ntOkkCw0VjRn1rIC"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.yFA2GaogSRYTonym"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":10,"title":"Features","_id":"2JmYi01IRovTVOQ8"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.RFV4bCMSRW9wWaV7"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":14,"title":"Features","_id":"oA6SEKBTvke2D4e6"}],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E69zz3w1zToNcZmT"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685718965387,"modifiedTime":1685719331366,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"oN86CosJJBoE8jpT"}
{"name":"Savant’s Calling","type":"subclass","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>For a very, very selective few, magic comes so naturally to them that they deal not with spells, but with the pure forces behind their creation. For a savant, rewriting magic is as easy as breathing, and mastering new skills as easy as a night spent ruminating on the subject. </p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc43\"><span><strong>Meditative Talents</strong></span> </h4><p>At 2nd level, you gain 1 magic talent. Whenever you complete a long rest, you can change this talent. You gain an additional talent you can change in this fashion at 10th and 18th levels.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc44\"><span><strong>Reflect Spell</strong></span></h4><p>At 5th level, when targeted by a spell or magic sphere effect, as a reaction you can expend martial focus to make an opposed spellcasting ability check. If successful, the spell is reflected back on the caster as if you were the caster and they were the target. Whether or not you are successful, you cannot take an Action on your next turn.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc45\"><span><strong>Quick Rumination</strong></span></h4><p>Beginning at 10th level, you can change your meditative talents during a short or long rest.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc46\"><span><strong>Greater Reflect Spell</strong></span></h4><p>At 14th level, you can use your action normally on the turn after using reflect spell and automatically regain your martial focus if your spellcasting ability check succeeds.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc47\"><span><strong>Instant Rumination</strong></span></h4><p>Beginning at 18th level, you can expend your martial focus to change a meditative talent as an Action.</p><hr /><h4 id=\"toc48\"><span><strong>Masterful Rumination</strong></span></h4><p>At 20th level, you can use instant rumination as a bonus action instead of an action.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sphres of Power","identifier":"savants-calling","classIdentifier":"prodigy","advancement":[{"_id":"KizCImelz0cLOWNQ","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.1zbImxcStiLRlzKu"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":2,"title":"Features"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.UyAEYZmNMEOkJXIH"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":10,"title":"Features","_id":"mTSDsiXe0J7tp9pt"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.EBlRNcugqO3Q0vSk"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":5,"title":"Features","_id":"k8o7twAJl6RbOwd1"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.SFauYz442ydCrgXO"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":14,"title":"Features","_id":"5QM8MCumuiAIrMjP"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.KTyL7Sb1r8xfHfWX"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":18,"title":"Features","_id":"Qle5LR8y5Gj0ZMN5"},{"type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.wolfer-spheres5e.subclass-features.GQttBTSz8vMoypqu"],"optional":false,"spell":{"ability":"","preparation":"","uses":{"max":"","per":""}}},"value":{},"level":20,"title":"Features","_id":"IdmoDzzXxADAbQK6"}],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hiekHoDAOyJs43Vf"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685723363178,"modifiedTime":1685724158687,"lastModifiedBy":"jvc9MjSXj7pOw4bp"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"sacsFMZMeMx5Ijp9"}
